  </p>

  <p>Updating of list-based suggestions (delayed simulating AJAX response)</p>

  <p>
    <input id="autocomplete-updatable" type="text"/>
  <ul id="suggestions-updatable" style="display: none">
    <li>Java</li>
    <li>Haskell</li>
  </ul>
  <script>
    var counter = 1;
    $("#autocomplete-updatable").richAutocomplete({
      source: document.getElementById('suggestions-updatable'),
      update: function (request, done) {
        setTimeout(function () {
          $('#suggestions-updatable').append($('<li>Test' + counter++ + '</li>'));
          done();
        }, 1000);
      }
    });
  </script>
  </p>

  <p>Autocomplete's creation, destruction, enabling and disabling:</p>

  <p>
    <input id="autocomplete-lifecycle" type="text"></input>
  <ul id="suggestions" style="display: none">
    <li>Java</li>
    <li>Haskell</li>
  </ul>
  <script>
    var options = { source: document.getElementById('suggestions'), showButton: true };
    $("#autocomplete-lifecycle").richAutocomplete(options);
  </script>
  </p>

